{"ID":270324, "Text":"<div class=\"page\"><div class=\"pageNum\"><a name=\"324\"><\/a><div class=\"prev\"><a href=\"stpjs323.html\">Prev<\/a><\/div><div class=\"next\"><a href=\"stpjs325.html\">Next<\/a><\/div>\n\t\t\t    STPJS 324<\/div>\n  <p class=\"cont\">down the streets with my scribe. Gave instructions to try those persons who were preaching,\n  teaching, or practicing the doctrine of plurality of wives; for, according to the law, I hold the keys\n  of this power in the last days; for there is never but one on earth<span class=\"footRef\">1<\/span> at a time on whom the power and\n  its keys are conferred; <i>and I have constantly said no man shall have but one wife at a time,<\/i><span class=\"footRef\">2<\/span> <i>unless<\/i>\n  <i>the Lord directs otherwise.<\/i><span class=\"footRef\">3<\/span> (Oct. 5, 1843.) DHC 6:46.<\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">THE PROPHET&rsquo;S REMARKS ON THE DEMISE OF JAMES ADAMS<\/div>\n  <div class=\"topic \">How Salvation Is Acquired<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">All men know that they must die.<span class=\"footRef\">4<\/span> And it is important that we should understand the reasons\n  and causes of our exposure to the vicissitudes of life and of death, and the designs and purposes of\n  God<span class=\"footRef\">5<\/span> in our coming into the world,<span class=\"footRef\">6<\/span> our sufferings<span class=\"footRef\">7<\/span> here, and our departure hence. What is the object\n  of our coming into existence,<span class=\"footRef\">8<\/span> then dying and falling away, to be here no more? It is but reasonable\n  to suppose that God would reveal something in reference to the matter, and it is a subject we ought\n  to study more than any other. We ought to study it day and night, for the world is ignorant in\n  reference to their true condition and relation. If we have any claim on our Heavenly Father for\n  anything, it is for knowledge on this important subject. Could we read and comprehend all that has\n  been written from the days of Adam,<span class=\"footRef\">9<\/span> on the relation of man to God and angels<span class=\"footRef\">10<\/span> in a future state,\n  we should know very little about it. Reading the experience of others, or the revelation given to\n  <i>them,<\/i> can never give <i>us<\/i> a comprehensive view of our condition and true relation to God. Knowledge\n  of these things<span class=\"footRef\">11<\/span> can only be obtained by experience through the ordinances of God<span class=\"footRef\">12<\/span> set forth for\n  that purpose. Could you gaze into heaven five minutes, you would know more than you would by\n  reading all that ever was written on the subject.<span class=\"footRef\">13<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">We are only capable of comprehending that certain things exist, which we may acquire by\n  certain fixed principles. If men would acquire salvation, they have got to be subject, before they\n  leave this world, to certain rules and principles, which were fixed by an unalterable decree<span class=\"footRef\">14<\/span> before\n  the world was.<span class=\"footRef\">15<\/span><\/p>\n  <div class=\"footnotes\">\n    <div class=\"footnote\">1. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116331\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116331)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116331)\">D&amp;C 132:7<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">2. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111381\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111381)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111381)\">Jacob 2:30<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">3. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116310\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116310)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116310)\">D&amp;C 132:1,34-39<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">4. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"106989\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 106989)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(106989)\">Eccl. 9:5<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111167\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111167)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111167)\">2 Ne. 9:4<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111920\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111920)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111920)\">Alma 12:27<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">5. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"113097\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 113097)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(113097)\">D&amp;C 3:1<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"114062\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 114062)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(114062)\">D&amp;C 58:3<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">6. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"117047\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 117047)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(117047)\">Abr. 3:24-26<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">7. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109302\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109302)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109302)\">Rom. 8:18<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109628\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109628)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109628)\">2 Cor. 1:7<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109647\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109647)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109647)\">2 Cor. 4:17<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110136\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110136)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110136)\">Heb. 